+    redis.asyncio.maint_notifications.MaintNotificationsPoolHandler
+    redis.asyncio.maint_notifications.MaintNotificationsConnectionHandler
+
+These mirror `TestMaintNotificationsPoolHandler` / `TestMaintNotificationsConnectionHandler`
+from `tests/maint_notifications/test_maint_notifications.py` (the sync/threading based
+suite), adapted to asyncio: handlers are `async def`, the pool lock is `asyncio.Lock`,
+and pool/connection collaborators are exercised with `Mock`/`AsyncMock` rather than a
+real pool or real sockets.
+
+The shared notification and config classes (`MaintenanceState`, `NodeMovingNotification`,
+`MaintNotificationsConfig`, ...) come from `redis.maint_notifications` and are not
+re-tested here -- only the async-specific handler classes are.
+
+NOTE: as of today's code, `redis.asyncio.maint_notifications` does not exist yet, so
+collecting this module is expected to fail with an ImportError. That failure is the
+proof that these tests are written against the (not yet implemented) async contract.
